<DOC><DOCNO> WSJ870403-0105 </DOCNO><HL> Lone Star Industries Venture</HL><DD> 04/03/87</DD><SO> WALL STREET JOURNAL (J)</SO><IN> LCE </IN><DATELINE> GREENWICH, Conn.  </DATELINE><TEXT>   Lone Star Industries Inc. said it formed a joint venture with Monier Ltd. to make and sell concrete railroad ties in North America.    Monier, based in Chatswood, New South Wales, Australia, makes building and construction products, and concrete ties. The venture, Lone Star Monier Concrete Tie Co., will operate a factory in Denver. It has a contract to produce 1.8 million concrete ties ordered by Burlington Northern Railroad, a unit of Burlington Northern Inc., for more than $30 million.    Lone Star produces and imports concrete products and construction materials. </TEXT></DOC>